Global setup:

* Download and install the wonderful version control system Git. On Ubuntu
  this can be done with the command 'sudo apt-get install git-core'.
* Type 'git config --global user.email <your.email@example.com>'. This will
  add a line to ~/.gitconfig .

Download repository:

* In a terminal, change to the directory where you want to put the code.
* Type 'git clone git://github.com/mattgibb/fibres.git'.